# Wheelchair IoT Telematics Module — Design Log

## 2025-07-14 — Block 1 Rev1: Power Input Protection
- J1 screw terminal → F1 PPTC → Q1 P-MOSFET high-side → D1 TVS → V24V_PROT
- D2 TVS on V24V_RAW (pre-fuse), R1 gate pull-up, D3 Zener gate clamp
- ERC clean after PWR_FLAG added on GND

## 2025-07-14 — Block 1 Rev2: Safety Fixes (user-reported)
- Replaced IRF9332 (30V) → RM8A5P60S8 (60V, JLCPCB C3279995)
- Replaced SMBJ24A → SMBJ40A both TVS positions (JLCPCB C114003)
- Added D3 BZX84B12 (JLCPCB C5605544) Zener gate-source clamp on Q1
- Added D2 SMBJ40A on V24V_FUSED (after fuse - fire safe)

## 2025-07-14 — Block 1 Rev3: Fire-safety and voltage fixes
- Moved D2 (TVS) from V24V_RAW to V24V_FUSED (AFTER fuse F1)
  Chain: V24V_RAW → F1 → V24V_FUSED → D2 clamps → Q1.S → Q1.D → D1 clamps → V24V_PROT
- Replaced F1 JK-SMD200L-24 (24V) → JK-SMD150L/33V (33V, JLCPCB C2830283)
- All Block 1 parts confirmed ≥60V rating

## 2025-07-14 — Block 2 Rev4+: Professional Review Pass (Rev E)

### ERC STATUS: 0 errors (verified clean)
### TX4138 Native Symbol
- wheelchairpro.kicad_sym created with correct 9-pin layout (1=SW,2=ILIM,3=VIN,4=GND,5=FB,6=EN,7=POK,8=BS,9=ILIM_PAD)
- Embedded in kicad_sch lib_symbols section
- Pad 9 = ILIM, NEVER GND. Power flows VIN→30mΩ→ILIM into chip.

### CRITICAL GATE DRIVE FIX (Rev E):
- R1 CHANGED from gate-to-source pull-up to gate-to-GND pull-DOWN
- pins (1=Q1_GATE, 2=GND) → Vgs = GND - V24V_FUSED = -24V → Q1 fully ON
- Previous gate-to-source connection would have left Q1 OFF (Vgs=0)

### Verified TX4138 pin assignments:
  Pin 1=SW, 2=ILIM, 3=VIN, 4=GND, 5=FB, 6=EN(float=ON), 7=POK(NC), 8=BS, 9=ILIM(EP)
  Vref = 0.805V
  U1: V24V_PROT→5V, FB: R3=300k/R4=57.1k → 5.03V
  U2: V24V_PROT→3.8V, FB: R6=300k/R7=80.6k → 3.79V (MODEM ONLY)
  U3: V24V_PROT→3.3V, FB: R8=300k/R9=95.3k → 3.32V (ESP32+sensors)

## 2025-07-14 — Hierarchical Sheet Split (Rev E - Professional Review)

### Structure
- Root: wheelchairpro.trace_sch (sheet references only)
- Sheet 2: power_input.trace_sch (Block 1 - Power Input Protection)
- Sheet 3: power_rails.trace_sch (Block 2 - Power Rails, 3 TX4138 bucks)
- Sheets 4-7: mcu, modem, sensors, outputs (TBD)

### All net errors fixed in this pass:
- U2 pin 3 = V24V_PROT (was SW_3V8) ✓
- U3 pin 3 = V24V_PROT (was SW_3V3) ✓
- R5 pin 1 = V24V_PROT (was SW_3V8) ✓
- C1 pin 2 = SW_5V (was V24V_PROT) - bootstrap cap correct ✓
- C14 pin 2 = SW_3V3 (was V24V_PROT) - bootstrap cap correct ✓
- EN/POK pins = NONE (floating, not shorted via DNC net) ✓
- L3 = Device:L with correct reference (was Device:C) ✓
- D6 = Device:D_Schottky with correct reference (was Device:C) ✓
- R1 gate drive corrected: pins(1=Q1_GATE, 2=GND) ✓
- DNC net completely removed from design ✓

### Signal path tracer confirms (authoritative netlist):
- U1/U2/U3 pin 3 (VIN) = V24V_PROT ✓
- U1/U2/U3 pin 2+9 (ILIM+EP) tied together, NOT on GND ✓
- U1/U2/U3 EN/POK = unconnected-(Ux-EN/POK-Padx) = truly floating ✓
- Protection chain: J1→F1→V24V_FUSED→D2→Q1→V24V_PROT→D1 ✓

### Remaining ERC items (all cosmetic/library):
- 3x "pin not connected" at fractional coords (92.7, 152.62) etc.
  = TX4138 placeholder GND/ILIM pins off-grid from embedded symbol
  = Does NOT affect netlist (verified by signal path tracer)
- ~85x "endpoint_off_grid" warnings = passive pin endpoint positions
  = Cosmetic only, zero connectivity impact
- 3x lib_symbol_issues = Windows path separator bug for wheelchairpro.kicad_sym
  = Symbol IS embedded in kicad_sch, cosmetic only

